{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Info\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These scripts let you create take markers called "SYNC" on all selected items at the edit cursor position using the script "soapy-bat_CreateSyncMarker.lua". The script "soapy-bat_SyncMarkerToCursor.lua" moves the selected items containing sync markers so that the sync markers align with the edit cursor. This functionality is inspired from Pro Tools' Sync Points.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Seahorse \u55356 ?\u57098 ? Tools for REAPER\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Multitrack Source-Destination editing using REAPER's Fixed Item Lanes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Introduction\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/feb693ca-bd95-44a1-9e46-bb7ecf1d34b2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55357 ?\u56613 ? Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u9986 ?\u65039 ? Three-point and four-point multitrack source-destination editing  \u55356 ?\u57255 ? Fade auditioning and quick editing using single keystrokes  \u55357 ?\u56453 ? extensive user preferences editable via GUI\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u9881 ?\u65039 ? Prerequisites\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.sws-extension.org/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
SWS Extension
}}}
\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
ReaPack
}}}
\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapertoolkit.dev/#1_reapack"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
Reaper Toolkit (rtk)
}}}
\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Head to {\i REAPER Preferences -> Editing Behavior} and set {\i Locked item ripple editing behavior: {\b Locked items are unaffected by ripple}}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab For multitrack editing, set all relevant tracks' {\i grouping parameters} to {\i {\b Media/Razor Edit Lead}} as well as {\i {\b Media/Razor Edit Follow}}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Activate {\i Options -> {\b Offset overlapping items vertically}} for better visibility\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab The scripts assume all source media / takes to reside in fixed item lanes. Comp Destination is the topmost lane.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55356 ?\u57119 ? How it works\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Make sure...\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u10004 ?\u65039 ? to read the {\b prerequisites} carefully.  \u10004 ?\u65039 ? your track groups' {\f1 Razor Edit Lead / Follow} parameters are set up as desired.  \u10004 ?\u65039 ? your source media is organized in {\b fixed item lanes} and there is at least {\b one empty lane} at the top. This will be your destination.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 \u9986 ?\u65039 ? 3-Point Edit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Place the source markers in the desired area of your source take.}  Select the source item (the lane does not have to be active). Place the edit cursor and run the scripts {\f1 SetSrcIn} or {\f1 SetSrcOut} respectively.  Switch to 'fast mode' in preferences where you can place source markers simply by hovering over the item.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Set one or two destination markers.}  Place the edit cursor and run the scripts {\f1 SetDstIn} or {\f1 SetDstOut} respectively.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Perform the Edit!}  Keep the source item selected, then run one of the three scripts:  - {\f1 3pointNoRipple}  - {\f1 3pointRipple}  - {\f1 4point}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 \u55356 ?\u57255 ? Fade Audition\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Hover the mouse over any item. To hear the fade closest to the mouse pointer, run one of the scripts:  \u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ? - {\f1 AuditionXFade} : You will hear the crossfade.  \u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ? - {\f1 AuditionXIn} : You will hear material up to the fade.  \u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ? - {\f1 AuditionXOut} : You will hear material after the fade.  \u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ? - {\f1 AuditionOIn} : You will hear the {\i left} side material {\i extended past} the fade.  \u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ?\u160 ? - {\f1 AuditionOOut} : You will hear the {\i right} side material {\i extended before} the fade.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Pre-roll and post-roll times are editable in the user preferences. More to come.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 \u55356 ?\u57242 ?\u65039 ? Quick Fade Edit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You might want to turn on ripple mode {\b (and off, after you're done)}. Activate {\i Options -> {\b Offset overlapping items vertically}} for better visibility. Consider having a look at the Snail \u55357 ?\u56332 ? Tools which might come in handy when ripple editing with media in fixed item lanes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Line up items at the cut.}  To make the waveform visible, use the script {\f1 ExtendItems}.  Hover over any item near its edge and run the script in order to extend the items' ends incrementally in opposite directions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Perform the Fade!}  Run the script {\f1 QuickFade} to place a quick standard fade at your mouse position. Sculpt the fade to taste.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Standard fade length and extension increments are editable in the user preferences.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 \u55357 ?\u56453 ? User Preferences\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Find all preferences concerning the seahorse scripts by running {\f1 soapy-seahorse_Preferences.lua}  Switch through tabs on the top right.  With text / number entries, don't forget to save using the {\i Apply} buttons.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u9889 ? Known Limitations\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab So far, the scripts only respect symmetrical crossfades. Asymmetrical crossfades have to be edited manually.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Certain operations will cause muted items to be unmuted. This will be resolved shortly.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Active development is in progress using REAPER 7.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Snail \u55357 ?\u56332 ? Tools for REAPER\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Lock items in Fixed Item Lanes when ripple editing. Useful complementary scripts to the source-destination workflow presented above.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Bat \u55358 ?\u56711 ? Tools for REAPER\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Quickly move items around using sync points.\par}
